This Python3 software resources implement decision aid algorithms useful in the field of 
Algorithmic Decision Theory and more specifically 
in outranking based Multiple Criteria Decision Aid (MCDA).

Technical documentation and tutorials are available under the following link:
http://leopold-loewenheim.uni.lu/docDigraph3/

Installation instructions:

On a (Unix, Mac OSX) command line using git or subversion:

...$git clone https://github.com/rbisdorff/Digraph3

or,

...$svn co http://leopold-loewenheim.uni.lu/svn/repos/Digraph3

cd to the extracted Digraph3 directory:

../Digraph3$ make install
installs (with sudo !!) the digraphs module in the current running python environment. 
Pythhon 3.5+ environment is recommemded. 

If the cython C-compiled modules for BigData are required, the Cython package must previously be 
installed in the running Python environment (...$ pip3.5+ install cython )

.. /Digraph3$ make tests
runs a nose test suite in the ./test directory
(python3 nose package required  ..$ pip3.5+ install nose )

.. /Digraph3$ make verboseTests
runs a verbose (with stdout not captured) nose test suite 

Enjoy !!
R Bisdorff
http://leopold-loewenheim.uni.lu/bisdorff/
